2025-01-27T09:25:35: Compound sharp-edged weir. Flows affected by Fruid Reservoir and diverted to Talla Reservoir.
Compound sharp-edged weir (9m wide) about 3km above the confluence with the Tweed. Fruid Reservoir opened 1968 for public water supply after station closed.
Flows in excess of 15.8cumecs are truncated and have to be estimated (this is said to occur once or twice per year). Theoretical rating for weir.
Mainly Silurian rock and boulder clay. Peat on high ground. High moorland; rough pasture; tree cover.
21.4 sq.km (90%) of catchment area controlled. Aqueduct diverts water to Talla Reservoir from 1954 onwards.
